## AhaDiff

When suggesting or reviewing code changes, use AhaDiff for verified learn-back:

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` for committed changes.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged work.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` and `ahadiff review` for retention.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` for existing runs.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` for targeted follow-up.
- `ahadiff serve` for local WebUI inspection.

Prefer explanations backed by `claims.jsonl` and file-line evidence. Treat
`.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` as local AhaDiff
state unless the repo policy says otherwise. Keep provider credentials in
environment variables and avoid committing private audit logs.
